{
  "texts": [
    "Minesweeper, known for its hidden information and unpredictability, exemplifies stochastic puzzles, requiring players to deduce mine locations from numerical clues, challenging spatial reasoning.",
    "Li et al. (2023) evaluated LLMs on Minesweeper, comparing table and coordinate representations.",
    "Even though GPT-3.5 displayed initial understanding, enhancements like few-shot prompting had minimal effects.",
    "Conversely, GPT-4 improved mine identification but struggled to complete boards, highlighting Minesweeper's role in evaluating LLMs' strategic thinking.",
    "Experiments favored the coordinate representation over the table format for aiding LLM comprehension."
  ]
}